{"user_message": {"title": "ADR 0001 — Case-File Criteria Aggregation Defect Fixed (Meridian / Immigration Paperwork)", "content": "## ADR 0001 — Centralize O-1A criteria status aggregation\n\n**Scope:** `src/features/case-file` · Status: Accepted · 2026-05-27\n\n### Context\nThe highest-priority correctness defect in the reviewed area was in `CriteriaTable.tsx:10,23`:\n\n```tsx\nconst met = criteria.filter((c) => c.status !== \"Partial\").length;\n{met} strong · 1 partial\n```\n\nThree grounded problems:\n1. **Hardcoded `1 partial`** — the partial count is a literal while qualifying is computed. Any change to `data.ts` (a 2nd `Partial`, a removed criterion) makes the eligibility badge *silently lie* — unacceptable on a legal/eligibility surface.\n2. **Unsafe data-shape assumption** — `status !== \"Partial\"` counts *any* non-Partial value (a typo, or an absent status from upstream Gemini/Document AI scoring) as qualifying, inflating the count.\n3. **Static `success` tone** regardless of whether the 3-criteria threshold is actually met.\n\n`src/lib/format.ts` was also inspected and found sound for its current numeric inputs — no change needed there.\n\n### Decision\nExtracted a pure aggregator `summarizeCriteria(items)` → `{ total, qualifying, partial, meetsThreshold }` with explicit `QUALIFYING_THRESHOLD = 3` in new `src/features/case-file/criteria.ts`. It counts only exact `Met`/`Strong` as qualifying, only `Partial` as partial, and **ignores malformed rows** (non-array input, unknown/absent status) instead of miscounting. `CriteriaTable.tsx` now derives every count and the badge tone from it.\n\n### Consequences\n- Eligibility read-out stays truthful as data evolves; tone reflects the real threshold.\n- **Render unchanged for current data** (7 qualifying · 1 partial · 8 evaluated, success tone) — verified.\n- `tsc --noEmit` clean. Aggregation is now unit-testable & reusable.\n- Established a lightweight `node:test` + `tsx` test convention (no test-runner dependency added).\n\n## Task breakdown (shipped this run + follow-ups) — 5 tasks · 8 pts\n\n| # | Task | Scope | Pts | Status |\n|---|------|-------|-----|--------|\n| 1 | Add `criteria.ts` aggregator | Pure `summarizeCriteria` + `QUALIFYING_THRESHOLD` | 2 | ✅ Done |\n| 2 | Wire `CriteriaTable` to aggregator | Replace hardcoded counts + threshold-based tone | 1 | ✅ Done |\n| 3 | Regression test `criteria.test.ts` | 4 cases incl. data-drift/malformed input (`tsx --test`) | 2 | ✅ Done (4/4 pass) |\n| 4 | Publish ADR to `docs/adr/0001-…md` | Decision log entry | 1 | ✅ Done |\n| 5 | Follow-up: drive `92% approval likelihood` (CaseFileDashboard.tsx) from real aggregation instead of literal | Same class of hardcoded-summary defect | 2 | ⏳ Proposed |\n\n**Verification:** `npx tsx --test src/features/case-file/criteria.test.ts` → 4 pass, 0 fail. `npx tsc --noEmit` → clean. No existing rendering broken.\n\nFiles changed: `src/features/case-file/criteria.ts` (new), `criteria.test.ts` (new), `components/CriteriaTable.tsx` (edited), `docs/adr/0001-criteria-status-aggregation.md` (new).", "content_type": "success", "priority": "normal"}}

